const content = "<div id=\"mm-0\">\n    <section id=\"j3FFGevBbx_r_j3FFGevBbx_r\"><div><div><div id=\"\"><div><h1 style=\"min-height:20px\">New York Mineral Rights</h1></div></div><div id=\"\"><div><div><p></p><p>Economic benefit from New York mineral rights date back to November 1865 when Job Moses' Hall Farm Petroleum Company discovered oil in Carrollton Township of Cattaraugus County. The Moses No. 1 well was drilled to 1,165 feet with initial production of only seven barrels per day. Recently, the Marcellus Shale has become a natural gas play made possible by advances in horizontal drilling and hydraulic fracturing. This shale play is located in the southern part of New York.</p><p><br></p><h2><strong>Major Oil and Gas Fields in New York</strong></h2><p><br></p><ul><li>Bradford Field</li><li>Caton Field</li><li>Cramer Hollow Field</li><li>Darling Creek Field</li><li>Five Mile Field</li><li>Forest Hill Field</li><li>Green Hill Field</li><li>Lakeshore Field</li><li>Quackenbush Hill Field</li><li>Rayner Field</li></ul><p><br></p><h2><strong>Oil and Gas Companies Active in New York</strong></h2><p><br></p><ul><li>Ardent Resources</li><li>Case Brothers</li><li>Chesapeake Energy</li><li>Copper Ridge Oil</li><li>Fortuna Energy</li><li>Hydrocarbon Generation</li><li>Nornew Inc</li><li>Stedman Energy</li></ul><h2><strong>New York Mineral Rights Links</strong></h2><p><br></p><p>New York State Department of Environmental Protection: <a href=\"http://www.dec.ny.gov/energy/205.html\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.dec.ny.gov/energy/205.html</a></p><p><br></p><p><strong>Additional Reading</strong></p><ul><li><a href=\"https://www.mineralwise.com/owners-guide/oil-and-gas-basics-for-mineral-owners\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">Oil &amp; Gas 101</a> – General information for mineral rights owners. Start here if you’re a newbie.</li><li><a href=\"https://www.mineralwise.com/directory/shale-plays/marcellus-shale-new-york\" rel=\"noopener